gomodel:SYNGO_3818  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: [Figure 4. Syt10 Is Essential for STFP-Induced LTP of G-M Synapses]\nFigure 5. IGF1 Induces Rapid Postsynaptic Potentiation of G-M Synapses Requiring IGF1-R Signaling\nFigure 6. IGF1-R Signaling Is Required by STFP-Induced LTP of G-M Synapses\n\nDiscussion: \"Odor exposure in a social context during STFP induces sustained Ca2+ entry in mitral cell dendrites and triggers both glutamate release and IGF1 exocytosis. IGF1 acts on IGF1-R and potentiates G-M synaptic strength by recruiting more GABA-R, which may be a synaptic substrate for the association of odor signals and social context.\". Experimental description: \"Adult mice (age between 3 to 5 months old) with or without prior viral injections were used \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-27" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3818" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

